<subSubSection pageId="127" pageNumber="886" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="127.[170,1377,3177,3489]" pageId="127" pageNumber="886">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sody" authorityYear="1928" box="[173,439,3247,3280]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="127" pageNumber="886" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="celebensis">Scotophilus celebensis</taxonomicName>
might be a subspecies of S. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Horsfield" baseAuthorityYear="1831" box="[843,929,3247,3280]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="127" pageNumber="886" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="heathii">heathii</taxonomicName>
because it appears to be recognized as primarily based on its disjunct distribution. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
