<subSubSection pageId="127" pageNumber="886" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="127.[170,1377,3177,3489]" pageId="127" pageNumber="886">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[172,430,3366,3399]" pageId="127" pageNumber="886">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 
<quantity box="[633,790,3366,3399]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.75" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="7.5" pageId="127" pageNumber="886" unit="mm" value="77.5" valueMax="80.0" valueMin="75.0">75-80 mm</quantity>
, tail 
<quantity box="[877,982,3366,3399]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="127" pageNumber="886" unit="mm" value="60.0">60 mm</quantity>
(one specimen), forearm 
<quantity box="[173,325,3405,3438]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.3" metricValueMax="6.4" metricValueMin="6.2" pageId="127" pageNumber="886" unit="mm" value="63.0" valueMax="64.0" valueMin="62.0">62-64 mm</quantity>
. The 
<collectingRegion box="[414,530,3405,3438]" country="Indonesia" name="Sulawesi Utara" pageId="127" pageNumber="886">Sulawesi</collectingRegion>
Yellow Bat is very similar to the Greater Asiatic Yellow Bat (S. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Horsfield" baseAuthorityYear="1831" box="[221,312,3449,3478]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="127" pageNumber="886" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="heathii">heathii</taxonomicName>
), but no morphological comparison has been made to differentiate them.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
